# Backend conventions (this service)

Follow Technoholics Slim 4 + Doctrine + PHP 8 standards (PSR-12, 4-space indent, max line ~100, single quotes).

## Layout

- Feature folders: `src/<Feature>/{Controllers,Services,Entities,Repositories,DTO,Exceptions,Transformers}/`
- Routes: `routes/*.php` (or documented app-specific layout)
- Tests under `tests/` mirroring modules
- Docs under `docs/`

## Patterns

- Repositories extend `AbstractRepository`; use field constants (no magic strings).
- Request DTOs: `BaseRequestDTO` + `#[Assert]` / `#[Sanitize]`; search DTOs: `BaseSearchDTO`.
- Controllers: `validateTenant()` when applicable; `ResponseHelper::success` / error helpers; OpenAPI `#[OA\...]`.
- Services: `$em->transactional()` for writes; convert to arrays/DTOs before `$em->clear()`.
- Exceptions: feature `Exceptions/` extending `Technoholics\Exception\*`; services throw, do not return error codes.
- Logger: project `FileLogger` only — never new up Monolog.
- Never commit secrets (`.env`); use env vars.

